        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Dec 15. 1876</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am very much obliged for the kind present of your ‘Life of a Scotch Naturalist’ which I have begun to read. I shall be greatly surprised if it does not interest me in a high degree, for I have read with extreme pleasure every one, as I believe, of your other biographies.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>I remain dear Sir, yours faithfully &amp; obliged | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD had received <hi rend="italic">Life of a Scotch naturalist: Thomas Edward</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9404.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Smiles 1876</ref>). Smiles had written many biographies, including <hi rend="italic">George Stephenson</hi>, and <hi rend="italic">Boulton and Watt</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9426.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Smiles 1857</ref> and 1865).</note>
        </div>        
            
